main event: An unidentified round object, much brighter than stars, was observed in Tensleep, Wyoming on December 3, 1957.
interesting points: The object was the size of a car and disappeared in 55 seconds,The sighting lasted for 1.5 hours,Two observers reported the sighting,The weather was high thin scattered clouds with visibility of 15 miles,The object was later concluded to possibly be the planet Venus.
witness description: Mrs. Tensleep, Wyoming, Age 50, Mrs. Tensleep, Wyoming, Age 29
